snippet: As a symbol of Englishness, the Anglican Church is, on the face of it, as anachronistic as warm beer, London fogs and the stiff upper lip with Sunday attendance at its 16,000 parish churches falling to less than one million.

headline.main: Archbishop Ranks as England's Top Non-Royal, in One of the World's Least Religious Countries
